PrecisAppointment of ALAIN PIETRONIRO of Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, who is a duly qualified engineer and Director of the Water Survey of Canada at Environment Canada, as the Canadian accredited officer to carry out the provisions of the Treaty between the United States and Great Britain relating to Boundary Waters, and questions arising between the United States and Canada, signed at Washington on January 11, 1909 and ratified by the Protocol of Exchange signed at Washington on May 5, 1910, with respect to the St. Mary and Milk Rivers, to hold office during pleasure.
